Comment_glosser: Etymologically, according to contributor: “túskaas, the number seven, is related to the instrumental prefix tux̱s- ‘with pointed end’, and refers to the seventh or index finger.” But there is no synchronically visible mathematical operation going on. Also, according to what the contributor says otherwise, some things seem to be unclear with this form.
According to contributor, 1⋅ is optional. The variant without it is given as alternative glossing.
